title: For Sale/Trade:  Bryco Jennings 9mm in glorious chrome
postcontent:
These old Ring of Fire pistols are starting to dry up. This one is a chrome model, late production, it has the CA suffix indicating that this gun was made to conform to California safety standards. Controversy later surrounded their delisting. Parts made for the Jiminez JA Nine interchange. This once has two mags, knife was used to prop it up and not included.

Though shunned by some, these once common and inexpensive firearms represent an important part of late 20th century American firearms history.
